scene.message:
Nanjo: I've never had penny{nl}
candy. Yamaoka wouldn't{nl}
allow it.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: That shopkeeper seems{nl}
to suspect us.{waitkey}But with these strange powers{nl}
of ours, are we still truly{nl}
human, I wonder?{waitkey}What do you think?{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Do kids these days even{nl}
eat penny candy?{waitkey}{clearbox}Me, I came here every day,{nl}
drawing raffles and stuff!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: A shop like this is{nl}
nice once in a while, but{nl}
aren't you forgetting we{nl}
have to go to the hospital?{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: I'm worried about{nl}
the school too. I just have{nl}
a bad feeling.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: There are some{nl}
surprisingly calm people{nl}
around. I'm impressed.{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: One bite buys a{nl}
thousand years; two, ten{nl}
thousand. The life-extending{nl}
taste of Sennen-Mannen Hall!{waitkey}Now, how about one?{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: ...{wait_fr:16}Are you a{nl}
real human?{wait_fr:32} Well, if you're a{nl}
customer, you're welcome.{waitkey}{ret}
